---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Rules & FAQs" sideBarActiveItemID="Rules">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Rules & FAQs</div>
  </div>

  <div class="accordion" id="faqAccordion">

    <!-- FAQ #1 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="accordion-header" id="faqHeading1">
        <h2 class="mb-0">
          <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faqCollapse1" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="faqCollapse1">
            <i class="lni lni-question-circle"></i> <strong>#1</strong> I'm from Wayanad, but I'd like to team up with my friend who's from Gir.
          </button>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div id="faqCollapse1" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="faqHeading1" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
        <div class="accordion-body">
          <i class="lni lni-reply"></i> Of course, it's perfectly fine for a team to include members from different houses.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <hr>

    <!-- FAQ #2 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="accordion-header" id="faqHeading2">
        <h2 class="mb-0">
          <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faqCollapse2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faqCollapse2">
            <i class="lni lni-question-circle"></i> <strong>#2</strong> I've already registered a few days ago as an individual participant. Now I wish to team up with another student who has the same issue as mine. What should I do?
          </button>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div id="faqCollapse2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="faqHeading2" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
        <div class="accordion-body">
          <i class="lni lni-reply"></i> <strong>Please re-submit the <a href="https://forms.gle/eD1WxU9sEWaEk2WL8" target="_blank">registration form</a> with the updated team member details.</strong> Either of you can submit. Our automated scripts will detect such cases and both of your previous responses will be discarded after processing. You will be issued one team ID.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <hr>

    <!-- FAQ #3 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="accordion-header" id="faqHeading3">
        <h2 class="mb-0">
          <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faqCollapse3" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faqCollapse3">
            <i class="lni lni-question-circle"></i> <strong>#3</strong> Will the organizers create the teams?
          </button>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div id="faqCollapse3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="faqHeading3" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
        <div class="accordion-body">
          <i class="lni lni-reply"></i> With around 700 IITM BS students present in our LogicLooM and ML Challenge groups (combined), we encourage you to form teams through discussions and by sharing your skills with each other. Collaboration is an important aspect of these events, so we highly recommend working together if possible.
          <p>However, if you're unable to find a team-mate, register 'solo'. <strong>Once registration closes and the data is processed, we will pair solo registrants into teams according to the following priority rules:</strong></p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Batch Similarity:</strong> We will prioritize pairing students from the same or adjacent batches.</li>
            <li><strong>Track Preference:</strong> We will ensure that team members are assigned to the same track they selected during registration.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>By following these rules, we aim to create balanced and compatible teams to enhance your event experience.</p>
          <p><strong>All participants will receive a confirmation auto-mail from 'no-reply wayanad' regarding the team allocation details and team ID.</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <hr>

    <!-- FAQ #4 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="accordion-header" id="faqHeading4">
        <h2 class="mb-0">
          <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faqCollapse4" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faqCollapse4">
            <i class="lni lni-question-circle"></i> <strong>#4</strong> What if I registered solo because I want to participate individually, rather than because I couldn't find a teammate?
          </button>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div id="faqCollapse4" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="faqHeading4" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
        <div class="accordion-body">
          <i class="lni lni-reply"></i> <strong>We understand that some participants may prefer to compete individually.</strong> If you possess the necessary skills (proficiency in Python and ML/NLP), please complete the <a href="https://forms.gle/HThDbun5qaDnF7oq9" target="_blank">Request Form</a>. Note that this form is for requesting individual participation and is not the registration form; you should have already submitted your registration form beforehand.
          <p>If you meet the criteria outlined in the Request Form, your request will be approved, and <strong>you will be excluded from the team allocation process.</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <hr>

    <!-- FAQ #5 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="accordion-header" id="faqHeading5">
        <h2 class="mb-0">
          <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faqCollapse5" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faqCollapse5">
            <i class="lni lni-question-circle"></i> <strong>#5</strong> I've already registered my '2 member' team, but now wish to add the 3rd participant. Am I allowed to make changes?
          </button>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div id="faqCollapse5" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="faqHeading5" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
        <div class="accordion-body">
          <i class="lni lni-reply"></i> You can't edit the previous response. Please re-submit the <a href="https://forms.gle/eD1WxU9sEWaEk2WL8" target="_blank">registration form</a> freshly with the updated team member details. Last response will be considered.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <hr>

    <!-- FAQ #6 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="accordion-header" id="faqHeading6">
        <h2 class="mb-0">
          <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faqCollapse6" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faqCollapse6">
            <i class="lni lni-question-circle"></i> <strong>#6</strong> Our team opted for the AI-Generated Text detection task. Can we modify our track as well?
          </button>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div id="faqCollapse6" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="faqHeading6" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
        <div class="accordion-body">
          <i class="lni lni-reply"></i> Yes, re-submit the <a href="https://forms.gle/eD1WxU9sEWaEk2WL8" target="_blank">registration form</a> freshly with the updated track choice. Any changes are possible until the deadline.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <hr>

    <!-- FAQ #7 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
      <div class="accordion-header" id="faqHeading7">
        <h2 class="mb-0">
          <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faqCollapse7" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faqCollapse7">
            <i class="lni lni-question-circle"></i> <strong>#7</strong> I'm a fresher and not aware of ML. Should I participate?
          </button>
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div id="faqCollapse7" class="accordion-collapse collapse" aria-labelledby="faqHeading7" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
        <div class="accordion-body">
          <i class="lni lni-reply"></i> Yes, absolutely! Beginners and freshers are welcome to join, and the event offers opportunities for learning and growth. You can team up with someone who has more experience or choose a track that suits your skill level.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <hr>

  </div>

  <!-- Include Bootstrap JS for the collapsible functionality -->
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0-alpha1/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"></script>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Deadlines</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement title="Submission: closed" />
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Notification: approx. 4 weeks after the submission deadline"
    >
      As the submitted papers are reviewed within the standard IEEE ESL review
      system, we cannot offer a fixed notification date. However, ESL aims to
      notify authors of the review outcome within 4 weeks of the submission
      deadline.
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Submission Guidelines</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement title="Length">
      Up to 4 pages in an IEEE double-column, single-blind, 10-pt format.
      More information on the format can be found <a
      class="link link-accent"
      href="https://ieee-ceda.org/publication/esl/esl-paper-submission"
      >here</a
    >.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement title="Review process">
      The review is processed by IEEE Embedded Systems Letters (ESL).
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement title="Publication">
      All accepted papers will be published in <a
        class="link link-accent"
        href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpl/RecentIssue.jsp?punumber=4563995"
        >IEEE ESL</a
      >.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement title="Presentation">
      Authors of accepted papers will have the opportunity to present their work
      at SeHAS@HIPEAC 2025 in Barcelona, Spain.
      To present a paper at SeHAS, the presenting author must register for the
      HiPEAC conference (see registration details).
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement title="Submission link">
      To submit your paper, please use the following link: <a
        class="link link-accent"
        href="https://mc.manuscriptcentral.com/les-ieee"
        >https://mc.manuscriptcentral.com/les-ieee</a
      >. <p></p><b
        ><span
          class="bg-red-100 text-red-800 text-xs font-medium me-2 px-2.5 py-0.5 rounded dark:bg-red-900 dark:text-red-300"
          >Important</span
        > To be considered for SeHAS 2025, select the check-box in step 6 in the
        ESL submission portal indicating that you would like your paper to be considered
        for presentation at a conference/workshop that has a tie-up with ESL.
      </b>
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>
